title: Damon Williams' TD in final seconds gives Atlantic Coast win in thriller over Providence
text:
Damon Williams' TD in final seconds gives Atlantic Coast win in thriller over Providence 
Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 12:27 am 
ATLANTIC COAST 42 
PROVIDENCE 35 
Star of the game: Damon Williams scored four rushing touchdowns, including the game-winner in the final seconds, for the visiting Stingrays. Williams had 164 yards rushing on just eight carries for Atlantic Coast (4-3). 
Turning point: Providence RB Jamauri Wakefield’s third rushing TD tied the game with 42 seconds remaining. Williams returned the kickoff 39 yards, setting up the Stingrays with first down on the Stallions’ 31 with 38 seconds left. Williams rushed for 28 yards on first down, and scored from a yard out two plays later. 
On defense: Stingrays LB Alvin Chavis recovered a fumble and ran it 41 yards for a TD early in the fourth quarter. ... The Stallions’ Tyler Vermilya intercepted Ashton Gonzales at the goal line late in the third quarter. 
Fast facts: The teams combined for four TD drives of four plays or less in the first half. ... QB Derrick McCants threw a 76-yard TD pass to Will Mallory in the first quarter for Providence (1-5). ... Atlantic Coast outscored Providence 21-7 in the fourth quarter. ... Wakefield ran for 251 yards on 32 carries. 
They said it: “Damon Williams is a hard worker. He just said, ‘Coach, give me the ball, give me the ball, give me the ball.’ So that’s what we did.” — Stingrays coach Matt Elliott Paul Monaghan , For the Times-Union
